Description: A sealing for an unknown object which included a palm-fibre cord, now gone: oval impression from an intaglio gem with a helmeted head, perhaps Ares or Athene, to right and a spear in front; the rest of the device is obscure, but may include two men in combat: the whole may be a combination of images to produce a single object (a gryllus). Adjacent is part of an impression from the same gem, showing the spear more clearly, and the edge of another seal. Unfired yellow-brown mud.
Curator's comments: Terracotta IV Donated: Egypt Exploration Society. Roman, probably second century AD.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3642)
